 \cos(a+b+c) = \cos(a+b)\cos(c) - \sin(a+b)\sin c= \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}, 
 \cos(a+b)\cos(c) - \sin a\sin c\cos b - \sin b\sin c\cos a = \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} 
 \cos(a+b)\cos(c) + \cos(a+c)\cos b+ \cos(b+c)\cos(a)= \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} + 2\cos a\cos b\cos c, 
